Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- A new research and 
supply base was commissioned at the Muxemm Institute of the 
Forestry Science Branch of the State Academy of Sciences 
according to the assistance plan between the DPRK Government and 
the UNDP. 
  The base will help industrialize the breeding of spores and 
making of cursing clods of earth and increase the production of 
mushrooms. 
  The inaugural ceremony Thursday was attended by 
Vice-Chairman 
of the State External Economic Affairs Commission Kim Chong-u 
and other officials concerned and resident representative of the 
UNDP in Korea G. Faruq Achikzad and officials of the UNDP 
mission. 
  Speeches were made there. 

